#: ../../using.rst:50
msgid "Installing Custom Fonts"
msgstr "Instalando Fuentes Personalizadas"

#: ../../using.rst:52
msgid "PC-BSD® includes `Google Noto <http://www.google.com/get/noto/>`_ which provide multi-lingual Sans and Serif fonts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:54
msgid "If you have a collection of fonts that you have downloaded or purchased, you can configure your PC-BSD® system to also use these fonts. Which utility you use depends upon which window manager you have logged into."
msgstr ""
"Si tiene una colección de fuentes que haya descargado o comprado, puede "
"configurar su sistema PC-BSD® para que también use esas fuentes. La utilería "
"que utilice depende de a qué gestor de ventanas se haya conectado."

#: ../../using.rst:57
msgid "many other fonts are available from :ref:`AppCafe®`. Check the \"Search all available PBI and packages\" box in the \"App Search\" tab to search for fonts. Any font installed using AppCafe® should not require any additional configuration to \"just work\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:60
msgid "To install custom fonts within KDE, go to :menuselection:`System Settings --> Font Management`. In :numref:`Figure %s: Using KDE's Font Installer to Install Custom Fonts <font1>`, \"All Fonts\" is currently selected under the \"Group\" column, showing all of the fonts installed on this system."
msgstr ""
"Para instalar fuentes personalizadas en KDE, vaya a :menuselection:`"
"Configuraciones del Sistema --> Administración de Fuentes`. En la :numref:`"
"Figura %s: Usando el Instalador de Fuentes de KDE para Instalar Fuentes "
"Personalizadas <font1>`, \"Todas las Fuentes\" está actualmente seleccionado "
"bajo la columna \"Grupo\", mostrando todas las fuentes instaladas en este "
"sistema."

#: ../../using.rst:67
msgid "To install your fonts, highlight \"Personal Fonts\" under the \"Group\" column, then click the \"+Add\" button. This will allow you to browse to the font you wish to add. You can add multiple fonts in the same directory by holding down the :kbd:`Ctrl` key while making your selection. Click the \"Open\" button, which will install the font for you. When it is finished, a pop-up message will indicate that you will need to restart any open applications for the font change to take affect. Your newly installed font(s) should now show up in the \"Personal Fonts\" section in the \"Group\" column and be available to the applications you use."
msgstr ""
"Para instalar sus fuentes seleccione \"Fuentes Personales\" en la columna \""
"Grupo\", después haga clic en el botón \"+Añadir\". Esto le permitirá buscar "
"la fuente que desee añadir. Puede añadir múltiples fuentes en el mismo "
"directorio manteniendo presionada la tecla :kbd:`Ctrl` mientras que hace su "
"selección. Haga clic en el botón \"Abrir\", el cual instalará las fuentes "
"para usted. Cuando finalice, un mensaje emergente le indicará que necesitará "
"reiniciar cualquier aplicación abierta para que el cambio de fuente tenga "
"efecto. Su(s) fuente(s) recientemente instalada(s) debería ahora aparecer en "
"la sección \"Fuentes Personales\" en la columna \"Grupo\" y estar disponible "
"para usarla por la aplicación."

#: ../../using.rst:72
msgid "To install custom fonts within GNOME, go to :menuselection:`Activities --> Files`. Navigate to the location of the font that you would like to install and either double-click the font name or select \"Font Viewer\" from the icon's right-click menu. This will open the font in Font Viewer, allowing you to view it. If you like the font, click the \"Install Font\" button to make it available to your applications. In the example shown in :numref:`Figure %s: Using Files to Install a Custom Font <font2>`, the user is installing the BlackFlag font."
msgstr ""
"Para instalar fuentes personalizadas en GNOME, vaya a :menuselection:`"
"Actividades --> Archivos`. Vaya a la localización de la fuente que quiera "
"instalar y haga doble clic en el nombre de la fuente o seleccione \"Visor de "
"Fuentes\" desde el menú de clic derecho del icono. Esto abrirá la fuente en "
"el Visor de Fuentes, permitiéndole visualizarla. Si le gusta la fuente, "
"presione el botón \"Instalar Fuente\" para hacerla disponible a sus "
"aplicaciones. En el ejemplo mostrado en la :numref:`Figura %s: Usando "
"Archivos para Instalar una Fuente Personalizada <font2>`, el usuario está "
"instalando la fuente BlackFlag."

#: ../../using.rst:81
msgid "To install custom fonts within XFCE, use :menuselection:`Applications --> System --> Thunar File Manager`. Once you browse to the location of the font and double- or right-click it, you will see the same Font Viewer used by GNOME."
msgstr ""
"Para instalar fuentes personalizadas en XFCE use :menuselection:`"
"Aplicaciones --> Sistema --> Administrador de Archivos Thunar`. Una vez que "
"busque la ubicación de la fuente y presione o haga clic derecho en ella, "
"verá el mismo Visor de Fuentes usado por GNOME."

#: ../../using.rst:84
msgid "If you prefer to install fonts from the command line, become the superuser and copy the downloaded font to the :file:`/usr/local/share/fonts/` directory. Then, refresh the fonts cache::"
msgstr ""
"Si prefiere instalar fuentes desde la línea de comandos, conéctese como "
"administrador y copie la fuente descargada en el directorio "
":file:`/usr/local/share/fonts/`. Después, actualice el cache de fuentes::"

#: ../../using.rst:93
msgid "Multimedia"
msgstr "Multimedia"

#: ../../using.rst:95
msgid "PC-BSD® has been pre-configured to support most multimedia formats and makes it easy to install most open source media applications using :ref:`AppCafe®`. PC-BSD® supports both `PulseAudio <https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/PulseAudio/>`_ and `OSS <http://opensound.com/>`_ so that applications using either sound server should work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:99
msgid "If you install your web browser using AppCafe®, you should be able to play most media formats, including YouTube videos, Internet radio, and many trailer and movie sites."
msgstr ""
"Si instala su navegador web usando AppCafe®, debería ser capaz de reproducir "
"la mayoría de los formatos multimedia, incluyendo videos de Youtube, radio "
"por Internet, y muchos sitios de trailers y películas."

#: ../../using.rst:102
msgid "If people are blue in YouTube videos, this is due to a known issue in flash which Adobe hasn't fixed for open source players. To resolve this issue, right-click an area in the video, select \"Settings\", then uncheck the box \"Enable hardware acceleration\". Alternately, install `Minitube <http://flavio.tordini.org/minitube>`_ using :ref:`AppCafe®` and use it to watch YouTube."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:106
msgid "if you happen to come across a file that you can not play in a web browser or media player, it is probably because it is in a proprietary format that requires a licensing fee or restricts distribution of the codec that is required to play that media format."
msgstr ""
"Si se encuentra con un archivo que no puede reproducir en el navegador web o "
"en el reproductor multimedia, es probable que sea un formato propietario que "
"requiere el pago de una licencia o restringe la distribución del codec que "
"se requiere para reproducir ese formato multimedia."

#: ../../using.rst:109
msgid "AppCafe® contains several dozen applications for playing and editing multimedia. It includes these popular applications (click the links to view screenshots):"
msgstr ""
"AppCafe® contiene varias docenas de aplicaciones para reproducir y editar "
"archivos multimedia. Incluye estas aplicaciones conocidas (presione los "
"enlaces para ver las capturas de pantalla):"

#: ../../using.rst:111
msgid "`aTunes <http://www.atunes.org/?page_id=5>`_: full-featured audio player and manager that can play mp3, ogg, wma, wav, flac, mp4 and radio streaming, allowing users to easily edit tags, organize music and rip audio CDs."
msgstr ""
"`aTunes <http://www.atunes.org/?page_id=5>`_: reproductor y administrador de "
"audio lleno de funciones que puede reproducir mp3, ogg, wma, wav, flac, mp4 "
"y streaming de radio, permitiendo a los usuarios editar fácilmente "
"etiquetas, organizar la música y copiar CDs de audio."

#: ../../using.rst:114
msgid "`Audacity <https://sourceforge.net/projects/audacity/?lang=en>`_: multilingual audio editor and recorder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:116
msgid "`DeaDBeeF <http://deadbeef.sourceforge.net/screenshots.html>`_: music player that supports most audio formats."
msgstr ""
"`DeaDBeeF <http://deadbeef.sourceforge.net/screenshots.html>`_: reproductor "
"de música que soporta la mayoría de los formatos de audio."

#: ../../using.rst:118
msgid "`Decibel <http://decibel.silent-blade.org/index.php?n=Main.Screenshots>`_: audio player built around a highly modular structure that lets the user disable completely the features he does not need. Able to play CDs directly."
msgstr ""
"`Decibel <http://decibel.silent-blade.org/index.php?n=Main.Screenshots>`_: "
"reproductor de audio hecho en torno a una estructura modular que le permite "
"al usuario deshabilitar completamente las características que no necesite. "
"Es capaz de reproducir CDs directamente."

#: ../../using.rst:121
msgid "`gtkpod <http://www.gtkpod.org/index.php?title=Screenshots>`_: graphical user interface for the Apple iPod."
msgstr ""
"`gtkpod <http://www.gtkpod.org/index.php?title=Screenshots>`_: interfaz "
"gráfica para el iPod de Apple."

#: ../../using.rst:123
msgid "`Miro <http://www.getmiro.com/download/screenshots/>`_: HD video player that can play almost any video file and offers over 6,000 free Internet TV shows and video podcasts."
msgstr ""
"`Miro <http://www.getmiro.com/download/screenshots/>`_:  reproductor de "
"vídeo HD que puede reproducir casi cualquier archivo de vídeo y ofrece mas "
"de 6,000 programas gratis de TV por Internet y podcasts de vídeo."

#: ../../using.rst:126
msgid "`SMPlayer <http://smplayer.sourceforge.net/>`_: universal media player that can handle any media format and play audio CDs, DVDs, (S)VCDs, TV/radio cards, YouTube™ and SHOUTcast™ streams. This is the default player used by :ref:`Mount Tray`."
msgstr ""
"`SMPlayer <http://smplayer.sourceforge.net/>`_: reproductor universal de "
"medios que puede manejar cualquier formato y reproducir CDs de audio, DVDs, "
"(S)VCDs, tarjetas de TV/radio, YouTube™y streams SHOUTcast™. Éste es el "
"reproductor predeterminado usado en la :ref:`Bandeja de Montaje`."

#: ../../using.rst:133
msgid "Kodi"
msgstr "Kodi"

#: ../../using.rst:135
msgid "`Kodi, formerly known as XBMC, <https://kodi.tv/>`_ is a GPL-licensed software media player and entertainment hub for digital media. It can play most audio and video formats, CDs and DVDs from a disk or image file, and even files inside ZIP and RAR archives. It can scan all of your media and automatically create a personalized library with album covers, descriptions, and fan art."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:139
msgid "During the installation of PC-BSD®, the installer provided an option to install Kodi. If you wish to install Kodi afterwards, use AppCafe®. Click \"App Search\" and search for \"pcbsd-meta-kodi\". Once installed, an entry for \"Media Center\" should be added to the \"Multimedia\" section of the application menu of your desktop. You can also start Kodi by typing :command:`kodi` from a command prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:143
msgid "If you have never used Kodi before, take some time to skim through the `Kodi Wiki Manual <http://kodi.wiki/>`_. The `Turn PC-BSD into a home theater forum post <https://forums.pcbsd.org/thread-19799.html>`_ contains a quick how-to for configuring Kodi."
msgstr ""
"Si nunca ha usado Kodi antes, tómese algo de tiempo para revisar el `Manual "
"Wiki de Kodi <http://kodi.wiki/>`_. El `Post sobre convertir PC-BSD en un "
"home theater <https://forums.pcbsd.org/thread-19799.html>`_ contiene una "
"guía rápida para configurar kodi."

#: ../../using.rst:150
msgid "PlexHome Theater"
msgstr "PlexHome Theater"

#: ../../using.rst:152
msgid "`Plex Home Theater <https://plex.tv/>`_ is a centralized media playback system. The central Plex Media Server streams media to many Plex player Apps which are used to view your media library and watch shows."
msgstr ""
"`Plex Home Theater <https://plex.tv/>`_ es un sistema de reproducción "
"multimedia centralizado. El Servidor central Plex Media transmite archivos "
"de medios a muchas Aplicaciones Plex reproductoras que se emplean para ver "
"sus bibliotecas multimeda y ver programas."

#: ../../using.rst:155
msgid "During the installation of PC-BSD®, the installer will have provided an option to install PlexHome Theater. If you wish to install it afterwards, use AppCafe®. Click the box \"Search all available PBI and packages\" and search for \"plexhometheater\". Once installed, an entry should be added to the \"Multimedia\" section of the application menu of your desktop. You can also start this application by typing :command:`plexhometheater` from a command prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../using.rst:159
msgid "Once installed, an entry for \"Plex Home Theater\" will also be added to the login manager so that you can login directly to the home theater instead of a desktop."
msgstr ""
"Una vez instalado, una entrada para \"Plex Home Theater\" también se añadirá "
"al administrador de acceso de manera que pueda accesar directamente al home "
"theater en vez de al escritorio."

#: ../../using.rst:161
msgid "The first time you run or log into Plex Home Theater, a wizard will check your audio settings and sign into your Plex account. If you do not have a Plex account yet, create one at `plex.tv <https://plex.tv/>`_. The wizard will give you a PIN code and an URL to enter the code. Once you enter the PIN, the wizard will connect and sign you in. You can now search for and watch media. To exit Plex, click the \"<\" then \"Quit\"."
msgstr ""
"La primera vez que ejecute o accese a Plex Home Theater, un asistente "
"comprobará sus configuraciones de audio y lo conectará a su cuenta Plex. Si "
"todavía no tiene una cuenta Plex, cree una en `plex.tv <https://plex.tv/>`_. "
"El asistente le dará un código PIN y una dirección URL para introducir el "
"código. Una vez que introduzca el PIN, el asistente le conectará y le "
"autenticará. Ahora podrá buscar y ver archivos multimedia. Para salir de "
"Plex, presione \"<\" y después en \"Salir\"."

